{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773350849088,"sessionID":"ses_31c0d9c49ffeNN6mZUuXZlrOk1","part":{"id":"prt_ce3f288a4001bfbHh96kSatmG5","sessionID":"ses_31c0d9c49ffeNN6mZUuXZlrOk1","messageID":"msg_ce3f264d3001Q4PtfUPcsFoWA4","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01VGuY54eAExG15Kw7Gmgmd9","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/AGENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/AGENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n2: \n3: This file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\n4: If you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n9: \n10: These are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n11: \n12: ### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n13: \n14: ```\n15: # CORRECT — runs local source directly\n16: bun dev <command> [args...]\n17: \n18: # WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\n19: wombo <command> [args...]\n20: ```\n21: \n22: **Why:** wombo is dogfooded — we develop it using itself. The global binary is a\n23: snapshot from the last release. If you use it, you're testing old code, not your\n24: changes. `bun dev` runs `bun src/index.ts` which executes the current working tree.\n25: \n26: **Examples:**\n27: ```sh\n28: bun dev help\n29: bun dev features list\n30: bun dev features add my-feat \"My Feature\" --priority high\n31: bun dev launch --dry-run --all-ready\n32: bun dev init --force\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### 2. Never publish to npm\n36: \n37: Distribution is GitHub-only. Users install via:\n38: ```sh\n39: bun install -g github:fulgidus/wombo\n40: ```\n41: Do not add `publishConfig`, do not run `npm publish`, do not add `.npmrc`.\n42: \n43: ### 3. Keep bun.lock committed\n44: \n45: The lockfile is committed for reproducible installs from GitHub. Always commit\n46: `bun.lock` after adding/removing/updating dependencies.\n47: \n48: ### 4. Do not commit user artifacts\n49: \n50: `wombo.json` and `.features.yml` in the repo root are for **dogfooding only** —\n51: they configure wombo's own development. They are gitignored in user projects.\n52: However, in this repo they ARE committed (the `.gitignore` actually excludes them\n53: from the repo — check before assuming they're tracked).\n54: \n55: **Wait, actually:** Check `.gitignore` — these files are excluded. The template at\n56: `src/templates/.features.yml` is the canonical source. The root `.features.yml` is\n57: for local development only.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## Project structure\n62: \n63: ```\n64: wombo/\n65:   package.json              # name: wombo-combo, version in sync with git tags\n66:   src/\n67:     index.ts                # CLI entry point, arg parsing, command routing\n68:     config.ts               # WomboConfig type, defaults, loader, validator\n69:     commands/\n70:       init.ts               # Interactive guided setup (Prompter class)\n71:       launch.ts             # Launch a wave of agents\n72:       resume.ts             # Resume a stopped wave\n73:       status.ts             # Show wave status\n74:       verify.ts             # Build verification\n75:       merge.ts              # Merge verified branches\n76:       retry.ts              # Retry a failed agent\n77:       cleanup.ts            # Remove worktrees and sessions\n78:       features/\n79:         list.ts, add.ts, set-status.ts, check.ts, archive.ts, show.ts\n80:     lib/\n81:       features.ts           # Feature file I/O, types, ensureFeaturesFile guard\n82:       state.ts              # Wave state persistence\n83:       prompt.ts             # Agent prompt generation\n84:       launcher.ts           # Process spawning\n85:       monitor.ts            # ProcessMonitor\n86:       worktree.ts           # Git worktree management\n87:       merger.ts             # Git merge operations\n88:       verifier.ts           # Build verification logic\n89:       ui.ts                 # Console dashboard\n90:       tui.ts                # neo-blessed TUI\n91:     templates/\n92:       .features.yml         # Template with full schema docs\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ## Coding conventions\n96: \n97: - **Runtime:** Bun (not Node). Use Bun APIs where available (`Bun.file()`,\n98:   `Bun.spawn()`, etc.), fall back to Node stdlib when Bun doesn't have a\n99:   direct equivalent.\n100: - **Language:** TypeScript, strict mode. Run `bun run typecheck` to verify.\n101: - **Modules:** ESM only (`\"type\": \"module\"` in package.json). Use `.js`\n102:   extensions in import paths (TypeScript resolves them to `.ts` at runtime in Bun).\n103: - **No external CLI frameworks.** Arg parsing is hand-rolled in `index.ts`.\n104:   This is intentional — it keeps the dependency tree minimal and gives full\n105:   control for agent-readiness features (schema introspection, etc.).\n106: - **YAML library:** `yaml` (v2). Use `YAML.parse()` / `YAML.stringify()`.\n107: - **No npm registry dependencies** for core functionality. `neo-blessed` is\n108:   the only large dependency (TUI). Keep it that way.\n109: \n110: ## Testing and verification\n111: \n112: ```sh\n113: # Type check (no emit)\n114: bun run typecheck\n115: \n116: # Build (outputs to dist/)\n117: bun run build\n118: \n119: # Run any command via dev\n120: bun dev help\n121: bun dev features check\n122: ```\n123: \n124: There is no test suite yet. When adding tests, use Bun's built-in test runner\n125: (`bun test`).\n126: \n127: ## Known quirks\n128: \n129: - **Bun readline + piped stdin:** `rl.question()` silently fails after readline\n130:   emits `close`. The `Prompter` class in `src/commands/init.ts` works around\n131:   this using `rl[Symbol.asyncIterator]()` with `process.stdout.write()`.\n132: - **YAML null vs empty array:** `yaml` parses `features:` (no items) as `null`,\n133:   not `[]`. `loadFeatures()` normalizes this: `parsed.features ?? []`.\n134: - **`import.meta.dir`:** Gives the directory of the current source file in Bun.\n135:   Used in `src/lib/features.ts` to resolve the template path.\n136: \n137: ## Feature backlog\n138: \n139: The active backlog lives in `.features.yml` (local, gitignored). Use\n140: `bun dev features list` to see it. The canonical template is at\n141: `src/templates/.features.yml`.\n142: \n143: ## Making changes\n144: \n145: 1. **Check the backlog:** `bun dev features list`\n146: 2. **Pick a feature/subtask:** `bun dev features show <id>`\n147: 3. **Mark it in-progress:** `bun dev features set-status <id> in_progress`\n148: 4. **Implement the change**\n149: 5. **Typecheck:** `bun run typecheck`\n150: 6. **Build:** `bun run build`\n151: 7. **Test manually:** `bun dev <relevant-command>`\n152: 8. **Mark done:** `bun dev features set-status <id> done`\n153: 9. **Commit** with a conventional commit message referencing the feature ID\n154: \n155: ## Version and release\n156: \n157: - Current version is in `package.json` → `\"version\"` field.\n158: - Git tags must match: tag `v0.0.1` ↔ `\"version\": \"0.0.1\"`.\n159: - Release workflow (when implemented) triggers on `v*` tag push to main.\n\n(End of file - total 159 lines)\n</content>","title":"AGENTS.md","metadata":{"preview":"# AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n\nThis file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\nIf you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n\n---\n\n## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n\nThese are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n\n### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n\n```\n# CORRECT — runs local source directly\nbun dev <command> [args...]\n\n# WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\nwombo <command> [args...]\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773350849081,"end":1773350849087}}}}
