{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351567662,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d95ffenGqgaxNYTZEsYh","part":{"id":"prt_ce3fd5923002B5HUAvxb8Jzk6I","sessionID":"ses_31c036d95ffenGqgaxNYTZEsYh","messageID":"msg_ce3fd518d001GvIdp9hQKXhODL","type":"text","text":"Let me review the detailed requirements against what exists:\n\n**Subtask 1:** The spec says \"The template should use placeholders (e.g. {{project}}) where appropriate so it can be customized per-project.\" The current `src/templates/wave-worker.md` is a static file with no placeholders. This needs to be enhanced.\n\n**Subtask 2:** Looking at `init.ts`, the agent template installation logic is already there (lines 176-204). It:\n- Creates `agent/` directory ✓\n- Writes wave-worker.md ✓\n- Prompts before overwrite ✓\n- Ensures `agent/` in configFiles ✓\n\nBut it doesn't apply any placeholder substitution when writing the template.\n\n**Subtask 3:** `ensureAgentDefinition` in `templates.ts` exists and is called from `launch.ts` ✓. But again, no placeholder substitution.\n\n**Subtask 4:** `verifyConfigFiles` in `worktree.ts` exists and is called after copying ✓.\n\nThe main gap is: **the template has no placeholders** as required by subtask 1. The spec specifically says to add `{{project}}` and similar placeholders. Let me also check if the init code applies any substitutions:\n\nLooking at init.ts line 190: `const agentTemplate = readFileSync(AGENT_TEMPLATE_PATH, \"utf-8\");` — no substitution is done. And in templates.ts `ensureAgentDefinition`, same pattern — raw template is used.\n\nSo the implementation is mostly complete but needs:\n1. Add placeholders to the wave-worker.md template\n2. Add placeholder substitution logic when installing the template (in both init and ensureAgentDefinition)\n\nLet me implement these improvements:","time":{"start":1773351567661,"end":1773351567661}}}
