{"type":"text","timestamp":1773351761233,"sessionID":"ses_31c036d95ffenGqgaxNYTZEsYh","part":{"id":"prt_ce4004852001tIpF8wnVqGmSus","sessionID":"ses_31c036d95ffenGqgaxNYTZEsYh","messageID":"msg_ce400411a001DNRIAM5KSOr9Ok","type":"text","text":"All subtasks are complete. Let me provide a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\nThe feature `agent-template-lifecycle` ensures wombo ships, installs, and maintains the wave-worker agent template throughout the lifecycle. Here's what each subtask covers:\n\n### Subtask 1: Ship wave-worker.md as a bundled template (`agent-template-file`)\n- **`src/templates/wave-worker.md`** — Updated to use `{{placeholders}}` instead of hardcoded values:\n  - `{{featuresFile}}` — the features YAML file path (e.g. `.features.yml`)\n  - `{{branchPrefix}}` — git branch prefix (e.g. `feature/`)\n  - `{{buildCommand}}` — build command (e.g. `bun run build`)\n  - `{{runtime}}` — project runtime description\n  - `{{project}}` — project directory name\n- **`src/lib/templates.ts`** — Added `renderAgentTemplate()` function that reads the template and substitutes all placeholders with config values\n\n### Subtask 2: Install agent template during `wombo init` (`agent-init-install`)\n- **`src/commands/init.ts`** — Already had the full implementation (creating `agent/` dir, writing template, prompting before overwrite, ensuring `agent/` in configFiles). Updated to use `renderAgentTemplate()` for placeholder substitution instead of raw file copy.\n\n### Subtask 3: Check agent definition on launch (`agent-launch-guard`)\n- **`src/commands/launch.ts`** — Already calls `ensureAgentDefinition()` at the start of `cmdLaunch()` (line 879)\n- **`src/lib/templates.ts`** — `ensureAgentDefinition()` already existed. Updated to use `renderAgentTemplate()` with placeholder substitution when reinstalling the missing template.\n\n### Subtask 4: Verify agent config files in worktrees (`agent-worktree-verify`)\n- **`src/lib/worktree.ts`** — Already had `verifyConfigFiles()` function that runs after every `copyConfigFiles()` call. It checks all config files (including `agent/`) exist in the worktree and logs colored warnings for any missing ones.\n\n### Build Verification\n- TypeScript typecheck: ✅ passes\n- Build (`bun run build`): ✅ passes (0.77 MB bundle in 13ms)","time":{"start":1773351761233,"end":1773351761233}}}
